creator: Civic Apps
descriptionHtml:
Become a civic citizen and engage with your city like never before by downloading the official app for Sterling, IL. With features like Government, Parks & Recreation, Services, Calendar, Community and Report an Issue you'll find it easier than ever to stay connected with your city with just a few taps on your mobile device.

Government and Parks & Recreation sections allow you to have all the important contact and destination information in your city with the click of a button. Learn about your city's history, demographics and elected officials. Find parks, facilities and points-of-interest along with information, phone numbers, maps and directions.

Use the Report an Issue section to report graffiti, potholes and other issues directly to the correct city department right from your phone. The issues are tracked from the initial report to resolution in the "My Reports" section and you will receive push notifications as your report progresses.

Stay informed and up-to-date on the latest happenings and upcoming events through the Calendar section.

Download your city's app and start engaging with your city on a more meaningful level. Become a civic citizen today!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
In this collection of updates, we've fixed issues and improved functionality for all apps in the MyCivic family (MyCivic Services, MyCivic 311, MyCivic Utilities, and MyCivic MyCity).
Here are some specific updates you might find, depending on the apps you use, of course!
MyCIty: The HTML Tabbed menu item displays List View correctly now, and several icons (Call, Directions, Website, and Hours) were updated to new images.
Utilities: We updated the Consumption log to a new logging service.
